Refactor HesWidgetsDesign components and add example application
- Updated HesWinShadowHelper to improve DWM API initialization and error handling. - Modified Singleton.h to use raw pointers instead of unique_ptr for instance management. - Added resource file for including custom font (HesAwesome.ttf). - Enhanced common_defs.h for better compatibility with Qt versions. - Cleaned up stdafx.h by removing Vulkan-related code and added a dedicated DisableVulkan.cmake script. - Created a new example application (HesWidgetsDesignExample) to demonstrate the usage of HesApplication and HesTheme. - Implemented a simple test application with UI for testing various features of HesWidgetsDesign. - Removed outdated build scripts (build.bat and build.sh) to streamline the build process. - Updated CMakeLists.txt to include necessary directories and resources for the example application.

Enhance CMake configuration and project structure for HesWidgetsDesign
- Updated CMakeLists.txt to improve compiler settings and platform-specific configurations. - Added support for dynamic loading of DWM API functions in HesWinShadowHelper. - Introduced a new CMake configuration file for package management. - Enhanced the example project to automatically create a default main.cpp if no source files are found. - Added build scripts for both Windows (build.bat) and Linux/macOS (build.sh) to streamline the build process. - Improved organization of source files and headers in the project structure. - Implemented installation rules for the library and example project.
